<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clash 2, Revolution 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Alejandro Sequeira scored his first goal  
for San Jose to help lead the Clash to a 2-1 victory over the New 
England Revolution on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ronald Cerritos added a goal and an assist for the Clash  
(13-10). 
</P>
<P>
	Sequeira, acquired from Tampa Bay for Raul Diaz Arce last month,  
broke a 1-1 tie in the 63rd minute as San Jose made the most of a 
one-man advantage. 
</P>
<P>
	The Revolution's Mario Gori was sent off with two minutes left  
in the first half after he received a red card for a two-footed 
tackle against Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
	Joe-Max Moore scored for the Revolution (8-15) after his shot  
was deflected by defender Mauricio Wright. The ball bounced right 
back to Moore, whose volley beat goalkeeper Joe Cannon inside the 
far post. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
