<HEADLINE> Cleveland Rockers Fire Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- The Cleveland Rockers fired head coach Linda  
Hill-MacDonald on Saturday following the team's 66-56 victory over 
New York. 
</P>
<P>
	The team also announced that assistant coach Susan Yow was also  
fired. 
</P>
<P>
	``We want to thank Linda and Susan for their contributions to  
this organization,'' Rockers' general manager Wayne Embry said in a 
news release. ``At this time, we feel it is in the best interest of 
the organization to move forward in a new direction.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Rockers finished their season by snapping an eight-game  
losing streak with a victory over the Eastern Conference champion 
Liberty. The Rockers were 7-25 and failed to make the playoffs this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill-MacDonald coached the Rockers since the WNBA's inception in  
1997. She had an overall record of 42-48, including last season's 
20-10 record and an Eastern Conference championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Hill-MacDonald could not be reached for comment Saturday.  
</P>
<P>
	The Rockers said they will begin their search for a new coach  
immediately. 
  	   	
</P>
