<HEADLINE> Perrot Service To Be Held Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- A memorial service will be held Monday for  
Houston Comets point guard Kim Perrot, who died Thursday after a 
long battle with cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	Texas A&AMP;M women's basketball coach Peggie Gillom was among those  
in the room when the 32-year-old Perrot died at a Houston hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Gillom was an assistant coach with the WNBA's Comets before  
taking the job at Texas A&AMP;M. 
</P>
<P>
	Gillom told KPRC-TV on Friday that she had gone to be with  
Perrot during her alternative treatment in Tijuana, Mexico. They 
returned together last weekend to Houston. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was fighting it to the end,'' Gillom said.  
</P>
<P>
	Gillom said Perrot touched so many lives, but she prefers that  
her friend be remembered for her on-the-court talent. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't see Kim in the bed suffering. I don't see Kim and her  
last breath. I see Kim Perrot on that floor, telling the Houston 
Comets what to do and schooling the rest of her opponents and being 
a pest,'' Gillom said. 
</P>
<P>
	A memorial service has been scheduled for 11 a.m. Monday at  
Second Baptist Church. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
