<HEADLINE> Nev. Brothel Makes Ventura Tribute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CARSON CITY, Nev. (AP) -- A Nevada brothel that pro  
wrestler-turned-Minnesota Gov. Jesse Ventura patronized decades ago 
is naming a bedroom suite in his honor. 
</P>
<P>
	The Moonlight Bunny Ranch, where prostitution is legal, is  
remodeling one of its rooms and naming it the ``Jesse (The Body) 
Ventura Suite.'' 
</P>
<P>
	It will be decorated with Navy SEAL regalia, professional  
wrestling memorabilia and ``anything to do with Jesse's career,'' 
ranch owner Dennis Hof said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Donations of decorations are being solicited via radio stations  
serving SEAL bases in California and Florida, and contributors will 
receive passes to the brothel, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventura will be sent a lifetime pass to the 45-year-old brothel,  
which he made famous in his best-selling autobiography, ``I Ain't 
Got Time to Bleed'' with tales of his visit there as a SEAL in the 
1970s. 
</P>
<P>
	Asked about the honor Friday, Ventura gave no comment.  
  	   	
</P>
