<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sosa Hits 50th, 51st Home Runs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Sammy Sosa hit his major-league leading 50th and  
51st home runs Saturday, becoming the fourth player to post 
consecutive 50-homer seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	With two out in the fourth against Colorado's John Thomson, Sosa  
hit a 1-2 pitch into the left-field bleachers to pull the Chicago 
Cubs within 2-1 of the Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	With two on and one out in the sixth, Sosa smashed a 2-1 pitch  
from Thomson into the right field seats to give the Cubs a 5-3 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa, who also hit two homers Friday, now leads Mark McGwire by  
three home runs. McGwire did not homer Saturday and has 48 this 
season. It was Sosa's 39th career multihomer game and sixth this 
year 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa, McGwire, Babe Ruth and Ken Griffey Jr. are the only  
players with consecutive 50-homer seasons. Sosa had 66 last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa is ahead of last year's pace. In 1998, he hit his 50th and  
51st homers in the Cubs' 130th game; Saturday was the Cubs' 121st 
game. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
