<HEADLINE> Cubs Activate Lance Johnson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago Cubs activated outfielder Lance  
Johnson from the disabled list Saturday and optioned pitcher Kyle 
Farnsworth to Triple-A Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson had been sidelined since June 10 with an abdominal  
strain and has appeared in only 54 games. He started in center 
field Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Farnsworth was 2-7 in 21 games, 15 starts, with a 6.17 ERA. He  
had given up 107 hits and 37 walks in 89 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cubs were using a six-man rotation with Farnsworth and will  
now revert back to a five-man. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
