<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Teen-Age Amusement Park Worker Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRISTOL, Conn., (AP) -- A 16-year-old amusement park worker died  
Saturday, hours after falling beneath a moving ride. 
</P>
<P>
	Matthew Henne was preparing to let passengers off ``The  
Tornado,'' at about 5 p.m. Friday when he fell and got caught under 
the spinning ride, said Richard Bisi, a spokesman at the Lake 
Compounce amusement park. 
</P>
<P>
	Firefighters freed Henne about 15 minutes later, and he was  
transported by helicopter to Hartford Hospital. He died about 3 
a.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	State officials have determined the ride did not malfunction,  
Bisi said. 
</P>
<P>
	The ride was closed Saturday ``out of deference to Matthew's  
family and our team members who have worked with Matt this 
season,'' he said. The rest of the park remained open. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
