<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-21 14:50:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Browns Sign Place-Kicker Boniol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Disappointed with their place kicking during  
the preseason, the Cleveland Browns signed veteran Chris Boniol on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Boniol, who has kicked for Dallas and Philadelphia in his  
five-year career, was released by the Eagles earlier this week. 
</P>
<P>
	He had an impressive workout for the Browns on Friday, Dwight  
Clark, Cleveland's director of football operations said Saturday 
before the Browns opened their new $283 million stadium with an 
exhibition game against the Minnesota Vikings. 
</P>
<P>
	Boniol, 27, was not in uniform for Saturday's game, but will  
begin working out with the team on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Cleveland has not given up on kickers Danny Kight or Phil  
Dawson, but Clark said the team's place kicking duties were ``wide 
open.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In the first two exhibition games, Dawson was 2-for-2 on field  
goals, including the game-winning kick in overtime against Dallas 
in the Hall of Fame Game. 
</P>
<P>
	Kight was 1-for-2, missing a 46-yarder at the end of regulation  
against the Cowboys. 
</P>
<P>
	Boniol made 27 of 28 field goal tries for the Cowboys in 1995, a  
96.4 percentage, the second highest in league history. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990821.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-21 10:00:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Teen Accused of Stealing 16 Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIDDLETOWN, Conn. (AP) -- A 15-year-old girl apparently didn't  
think it strange that her boyfriend drove a different car every 
time he came to visit. 
</P>
<P>
	Police did. They arrested the girl's teen-age beau on Thursday,  
accusing him of stealing 16 cars in two months. 
</P>
<P>
	All the cars were stolen from the same area at the same time of  
night, beginning in early June, and were recovered the next day, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The case was cracked with the use of records from cellular phone  
calls made from some of the stolen cars. Police said the calls led 
them to the girl's home in Hamden, some 20 miles away. 
</P>
<P>
	The 15-year-old suspect, whose name was not released because of  
his age, was charged with multiple counts of larceny and criminal 
mischief. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
