<HEADLINE> Elliott Has Kidney Complication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- San Antonio Spurs forward Sean Elliott was  
back in surgery Saturday after doctors realized the kidney he 
received from his brother in a transplant was not properly 
connected. 
</P>
<P>
	Doctors at Methodist Surgery and Transplant Hospital noticed  
early Friday morning that urine was leaking from the place where 
the kidney and the bladder meet. The transplant was performed 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Elliott's organs were quickly repaired, the hospital said.  
</P>
<P>
	The 10-year NBA veteran needed the kidney because of an illness  
called focal segmental glomerular sclerosis. Essentially, Elliott's 
kidneys were unable to filter waste out of his blood. 
</P>
<P>
	So Elliott's older brother, Noel, stepped in. Noel Elliott was  
released from the hospital Friday, four days after donating one of 
his kidneys to his brother. 
</P>
<P>
	Doctors say Sean Elliott, 31, will be released next week.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
