<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  NFL Official Hurt in Cleveland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- NFL official Ron Liebsack suffered a broken leg  
and sprained knee Saturday night during the exhibition game between 
the Cleveland Browns and Minnesota Vikings. 
</P>
<P>
	Liebsack, a side judge covering the goal line, had thrown a  
penalty flag when Browns running back Terry Kirby fell out of 
bounds, rolling up on Liebsack's left leg. The accident occurred 
late in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Liebsack laid on the ground for a few minutes and was eventually  
carted off the field. 
</P>
<P>
	Kirby caught a pass from Browns quarterback Ty Detmer in the  
middle of the field, cut outside and was trying to break into the 
end zone when he hit Liebsack. The Browns were called for holding 
on the play. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
